definition.value: A 17-oxo steroid that is estra-1,3,5(10)-triene substituted by an hydroxy group at position 3 and an oxo group at position 17.
A phosphatidylglycerol in which one of the hydroxy groups of the glycerol moiety has been converted to the corresponding dihydrogen phosphate.

A scyllo-inositol phosphate compound having the phosphate group at the 6-position, guanidino groups replacing hydroxy functions at the 1-position and an alpha-L-lyxofuranosyl residue at the 4-position.
The L enantiomer of sorbose, a ketone-containing hexose (a six-carbon monosaccharide).
